cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL, cs.CR 

The paper proposes a novel learning paradigm for Deep Neural Networks (DNN) using Boolean logic algebra. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the effectiveness of the proposed framework in learning Boolean functions and discrete-algorithmic tasks, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also proposes a new framework for learning inductive logic programming (ILP) problems, which is a subfield of cs.AI. The paper uses neural networks, which falls under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses the interpretation of the learned logical functions, which falls under the category of cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper proposes a new solver for ILP problems, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
